file.name: api.yaml
file.content:
openapi: 3.0.0
info:
  version: '1.0.0'
  title: 'Organisation information'
  description: 'Fetch organisation information from different databases'
  #termsOfService: terms url goes here
  contact:
    name: developer name
    #email: email goes here
    #url: url goes here
  license:
    name: Apache 2.0

servers:
# Added by API Auto Mocking Plugin
  - description: SwaggerHub API Auto Mocking
    url: https://virtserver.swaggerhub.com/jon_test/organisation_api/1.0.0
  - description: 'localhost'
    url: http://localhost:8083

paths:
  /organisation/{organisation_name}/{member_name}:
    get:
      description: 'Obtain information about members of an organisation'
      parameters:
      - name: organisation_name
        in: path
        description: 'Name of the organisation'
        required: true
        schema:
          type: string
          example: Maersk
      - name: member_name
        in: path
        description: 'Name of the member to fetch'
        required: true
        schema:
          type: string
          example: Pete
      responses:
        '200':
          description: successful fetch of member
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                type: object
                properties:
                  id:
                    type: integer
                    example: 4
                  name:
                    type: string
                    example: 'pete'
